cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.HC 

This paper focuses on the sharing economy platform of Airbnb and its impact on socio-economic conditions in different areas of London. It involves data analysis and algorithmic regulation, which are relevant to several sub-categories of computer science. Specifically, cs.CY (Computers and Society) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the social and economic implications of a technology platform. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks) are also relevant as the paper analyzes the impact of Airbnb on social and economic networks. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper involves crawling and analyzing data from the web. Finally, cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the paper discusses the need for responsive regulations that take into account real-time demands.
